{"question_id": "Q004", "question": "Why does TabNet argue that tabular data is difficult for standard deep neural networks?", "ground_truth": "TabNet argues that standard deep networks are often poorly suited to tabular data because they lack the right inductive bias, can be overparameterized for tabular decision boundaries, and are often outperformed by tree-based methods that are efficient, interpretable, and fast.", "category": "definition_explanation", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "Tabular data has yet to see success with a canonical architecture for deep neural networks.", "token_f1": 0.24, "rouge_l": 0.1071, "correctness": 0.24, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 44.6039, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 2335, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.16767731308937073, "top_k": 9, "rerank_threshold": 0.3717964291572571, "source_diversity": 0.6596023440361023}, "reward": -0.1613, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.3831021562218666, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.37892934679985046, "strictness_score": 0.24289828538894653}, "reward": -0.2408, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.6217776462435722, "citation_strictness": 0.49769778130576015, "max_tokens": 683, "answer_detail_level": 0.5727828145027161}, "reward": -0.2746, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.1898828148841858, "confidence_threshold": 0.23976534605026245}, "reward": 0.677, "done": true}]}
{"question_id": "Q005", "question": "How do the encoder and decoder stacks differ in the Transformer architecture?", "ground_truth": "The encoder has repeated layers with self-attention and feed-forward sublayers, while the decoder adds an extra sublayer that attends over the encoder output and also uses masked self-attention so it cannot look ahead to future positions.", "category": "intra_paper_comparison", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The encoder and decoder stacks differ in that the decoder inserts a third sub-layer, which performs multi-head attention over the output of the encoder stack, whereas the encoder has two sub-layers: a multi-head self-attention mechanism and a simple, position-wise fully connected feed-forward network.", "token_f1": 0.3768, "rouge_l": 0.2247, "correctness": 0.3768, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 0.5, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 40.3068, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 2091, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.2932499051094055, "top_k": 8, "rerank_threshold": 0.4920886429026723, "source_diversity": 0.7295693010091782}, "reward": -0.1445, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.3208405077457428, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.3796975612640381, "strictness_score": 0.2504308521747589}, "reward": -0.2254, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.7727984488010406, "citation_strictness": 0.6113800257444382, "max_tokens": 596, "answer_detail_level": 0.5690321773290634}, "reward": -0.2593, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.1678975522518158, "confidence_threshold": 0.29