{"question_id": "Q006", "question": "How does BERT's masked language model objective differ from next sentence prediction?", "ground_truth": "Masked language modeling predicts masked tokens from context within the input, while next sentence prediction trains the model to decide whether sentence B truly follows sentence A.", "category": "intra_paper_comparison", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "BERT's masked language model objective differs from next sentence prediction in that they are two separate tasks used in pre-training. \n\nThe masked language model enables the representation to fuse the left and the right context, allowing for pre-training of a deep bidirectional Transformer (Document [2], Page 2). \n\nIn contrast, the next sentence prediction task jointly pre-trains text-pair representations (Document [2], Page 2).", "token_f1": 0.3429, "rouge_l": 0.2128, "correctness": 0.3429, "faithfulness": 0.3333, "citation_support": 0.3333, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 2, "latency_seconds": 41.6158, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 3081, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.1682662069797516, "top_k": 9, "rerank_threshold": 0.3707531988620758, "source_diversity": 0.6604008376598358}, "reward": -0.141, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.3785097375512123, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.3739371597766876, "strictness_score": 0.24066603183746338}, "reward": -0.2038, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.6291757673025131, "citation_strictness": 0.5055815810337663, "max_tokens": 680, "answer_detail_level": 0.574923537671566}, "reward": -0.2497, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.20484983921051025, "confidence_threshold": 0.23763933777809143}, "reward": 0.3252, "done": true}]}
{"question_id": "Q007", "question": "According to Figure 1 in the ResNet paper, what happens to training and test error when moving from a 20-layer plain network to a 56-layer plain network on CIFAR-10?", "ground_truth": "The deeper 56-layer plain network has higher training error and higher test error than the 20-layer plain network.", "category": "figure_table_diagram_grounded", "difficulty": "easy", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The deeper 56-layer plain network has higher training error, and thus test error, on CIFAR-10.", "token_f1": 0.8, "rouge_l": 0.7027, "correctness": 0.8, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 57.057, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 2611, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.23327121138572693, "top_k": 12, "rerank_threshold": 0.38043351471424103, "source_diversity": 0.6191580593585968}, "reward": -0.169, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.3092832863330841, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.3879926949739456, "strictness_score": 0.28557203710079193}, "reward": -0.3088, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.618789829313755, "citation_strictness": 0.6381244957447052, "max_tokens": 665, "answer_detail_level": 0.5216529127210379}, "reward": -0.3378, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.24448445439338684, "confidence_threshold": 0.20300906896591187}, "reward": 0.6147, "done": true}]}
{"question_id": "Q008", "question": "According to Figure 2 in the ResNet paper, what role does the identity shortcut play in the residual block?", "ground_truth": "The identity shortcut carries the input directly forward and adds it to the learned residual branch, so the block outputs F(x) + x.", "category": "figure_table_diagram_grounded", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The identity shortcut in the residual block performs element-wise addition with the output of the residual mapping.", "token_f1": 0.303, "rouge_l": 0.2927, "correctness": 0.303, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 1.0, "source_recall": 1.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 51.5264, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 3446, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.23850160837173462, "top_k": 12, "rerank_threshold": 0.35608337819576263, "source_diversity": 0.6440897285938263}, "reward": -0.1346, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.3023582547903061, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.37334349751472473, "strictness_score": 0.28444984555244446}, "reward": -0.3049, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.607334591448307, "citation_strictness": 0.6302687674760818, "max_tokens": 665, "answer_detail_level": 0.5377408303320408}, "reward": -0.3558, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": "verifier", "action": "verify_answer", "params": {"support_threshold": 0.2206595242023468, "confidence_threshold": 0.21246924996376038}, "reward": 0.6424, "done": true}]}
